name: Jenn Plowman
text:
I, unlike many others, did not have an appointment issue or wait for weeks to be called back. That part was fine. However, the professionalism of their “secretary” at the Tuscaloosa location was nonexistent. She was too young to be given that type of responsibility. The 2 photographers were super nice... no complaints there. BUT THEN, our proofs come in and we check out the prices. W O W. Can you say OVERPRICED?!?! Most of my son’s shots are great and I would love to have some prints made but who in their right mind would pay those prices???? The “better” deal, yet still crazy expensive, is to get a package, but that’s such a waste. No one cares about 50+ wallet pictures. That’s silly. So why order something that you won’t use?!
So, I gave 2 stars only because the pictures themselves were great.... based on everything else, 1 star!!!! If they sell enough of those price-gouged prints they can afford to buy their own stars 😡

name: Lisa Bailey
text: I was very disappointed with how the senior portrait session was set up. We were given a time to be there, but when we show up there were 8 other students there also and 3 photographers. One of the photographers also was taking money and checking people in. My son's pictures were not good. His shirt clashed with his background. They easily could have changed the background, but because they were so rushed they didn't. I over heard a photographer saying they really want had lunch or much of a break. I was just very dissatisfied because this was a time as a mom I've anticipated and looked forward to. It should have been a fun and good experience, but it was neither. When I got his pictures back, I'm even more disappointed. The problem is I have to use 2 of these pictures for his year book 😓 I can't find one that I like. I'm just really frustrated.
